OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1774569807
OL,3,CPharmacy staff reveal extent of
OL,4,C'escalating' abuse from patients
OL,6,FThe poll, which was conducted by
OL,7,FCommunity Pharmacy England - the
OL,8,Fofficial body that represents all NHS
OL,9,Fcommunity pharmacies in England -
OL,10,Ffound that a fifth of the 289 pharmacy
OL,11,Fowners surveyed endure verbal abuse on
OL,12,Fa daily basis.
OL,14,FMr Sanjay said he blames increased
OL,15,Fpressures brought about by the Covid
OL,16,Fpandemic for the trend.
OL,18,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,19,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,20,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,21,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1774569807
OL,3,CPharmacy staff reveal extent of
OL,4,C'escalating' abuse from patients
OL,6,F"I think it's the pressures that have
OL,7,Famounted to pharmacy, if you like,
OL,8,Fsince Covid," he added. "We are
OL,9,Fessentially a walk in centre for all
OL,10,Fservices. We need some support."
OL,12,FSome of the key findings to emerge
OL,13,Ffrom the survey included that three
OL,14,Fquarters of pharmacy owners suffered
OL,15,Fverbal abuse every week, and more than
OL,16,Fhalf (55%) had encountered it in the
OL,17,Flast six months.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1774569807
OL,3,CPharmacy staff reveal extent of
OL,4,C'escalating' abuse from patients
OL,6,FWhile physical abuse was less common,
OL,7,F6% of pharmacies reported assaults in
OL,8,Fthe last six months, ranging from
OL,9,Fstrangulation, pushing, punching and
OL,10,Fattacks after closing time.
OL,12,FAmy Fancrulli, a dispenser at Mr
OL,13,FSanjay's pharmacy, said she had "been
OL,14,Fnearly punched" by a customer "because
OL,15,Ftheir prescription wasn't ready".
OL,17,FShe said: "We've had a thief before.
OL,18,FThere was racist abuse and then we
OL,19,Fcalled them and they wanted to beat me
OL,20,Fup outside, so it can happen pretty
OL,21,Foften. When it does it is scary."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1774569807
OL,3,CPharmacy staff reveal extent of
OL,4,C'escalating' abuse from patients
OL,6,FCommunity Pharmacy England, in
OL,7,Fresponse to its research, is calling
OL,8,Ffor stronger protection for workers,
OL,9,Fas well as a zero-tolerance approach
OL,10,Fto violence or threats.
OL,12,FThe organisation's chief executive,
OL,13,FJanet Morrison, said: "Pharmacy teams
OL,14,Fare the backbone of community
OL,15,Fhealthcare.
OL,17,F"They should never face any kind of
OL,18,Fabuse, racism, discrimination, threats
OL,19,For violence just for doing their jobs.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1774569807
OL,3,CPharmacy staff reveal extent of
OL,4,C'escalating' abuse from patients
OL,6,F"These findings reflect escalating
OL,7,Fabuse in one of the NHS's most
OL,8,Faccessible frontline services and they
OL,9,Fshow an urgent need for stronger
OL,10,Fsystem-wide protections.
OL,12,F"Pharmacy staff deserve to be treated
OL,13,Fwith kindness and respect."
OL,15,FThe government has said NHS England
OL,16,Fwill work with pharmacists to address
OL,17,Fthe issues raised in Community
OL,18,FPharmacy England's survey.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
